@page
@model SailScores.Web.Pages.Help.IndexModel
@{
    Layout = "/Pages/Help/_HelpLayout.cshtml";
    ViewData["Title"] = "SailScores Help";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p>Welcome to the SailScores help center.</p>
<p>
    Our goal is to keep SailScores intuitive and easy to use without needing documentation.
    But if you're curious, troubleshooting, or just want to dig deeper, these pages are here
    to support you.
</p>
<p>
    We’re actively expanding this section over the 2025–26 winter. If there’s
    something you’d like explained or clarified, we’d love to
    <a href="mailto:info@sailscores.com">hear from you.</a>
</p>
<p>
    Here's what you'll find:
</p>

<section id="faq">
    <a asp-page="/Help/FAQ"><h3>FAQ</h3></a>
    <p>Quick answers to common questions about SailScores&mdash;perfect for new users or anyone needing a refresher.</p>
</section>

<section id="getting-started">
    <a asp-page="/Help/GettingStarted"><h3>Getting Started</h3></a>
    <p>A step-by-step guide to setting up your club, creating series, and understanding the basics of scoring.</p>
</section>

<section id="deep-dive">
    <a asp-page="/Help/Reference"><h3>Deep Dive</h3></a>
    <p>
        Explore advanced scoring features, tips for scorekeepers, and technical insights for curious sailors. This section combines:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Advanced Scoring &amp; Tips</li>
        <li>About &amp; Reference</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Here you'll find:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Insights into SailScores’ values, data practices, and technical design</li>
        <li>Tips for speeding up score entry</li>
        <li>Guides into the advanced features of SailScores</li>
        <li>Troubleshooting tips</li>
    </ul>
</section>
